{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated function signature matches the expected interface (parameter names, types, return type) specified in the description.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM output formatting and interpretation of the natural-language spec. A mocked generator can easily miss real signature drift/mis-typing failures.","test_description":"Call the real generation model with a strict interface spec (including typed params and return type), parse the produced function signature, and assert exact match. Run multiple times to surface non-deterministic signature deviations.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated implementation passes all provided test cases on the first or a subsequent attempt.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure boundary includes real code execution against a real test runner/subprocess/filesystem. In-process mocks of execution can hide import/runtime/environment failures.","test_description":"Run the service end-to-end with real test execution infrastructure (actual test files and runner invocation), using controlled generation outputs that pass either on attempt 1 or attempt 2, and assert the service reports success only when the real suite passes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.5,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When tests fail, the refinement step includes the failure messages in the next LLM prompt so the model can learn from its mistakes.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is prompt-construction wiring across modules (test-result capture -> prompt builder -> LLM request payload). Pure unit tests can miss cross-module field mapping/serialization defects.","test_description":"Use real test-failure artifacts from a failing run, pass them through the refinement pipeline, and assert the next LLM request payload contains the exact failure messages (including stack traces/special chars) in the expected prompt section.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The service stops after 3 failed attempts and returns a structured error with all three attempts and their test results.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is retry-loop and error-schema orchestration logic across generator/tester/result-collector modules. A single-function unit test is too narrow and can miss accumulator/state wiring bugs.","test_description":"Drive the service with deterministic always-failing generation outputs and failing test results, execute the full retry coordinator, then assert: exactly 3 attempts occurred, no 4th call was made, and the returned error object contains all 3 attempt payloads with their test outcomes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full loop — generate, test, refine, test again — produces a working implementation for a function that a single LLM call typically gets wrong.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This explicitly requires multiple sequential real agentic steps where later success depends on prior failure feedback. Single-step agentic or mocked orchestration would miss true pipeline behavior.","test_description":"Use a benchmark prompt known to usually fail on first generation. Run the real pipeline with real LLM calls across multiple attempts, real test execution each round, and assert eventual pass only after at least one refine cycle; record attempt-by-attempt artifacts to confirm causal progression.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.65}}]}
